{%- comment -%}
  Defer BSS B2B scripts so they don't render-block the main thread.

  Original was `{{ 'X' | asset_url | script_tag }}` which emits a
  blocking <script>. The 930 KB bss-b2b-js.js was preventing
  lazysizes from running on heavy collection landing pages
  (Schwarzkopf, TIGI, K18) — product images stayed grey, page hung.

  defer is safe here: BSS B2B init runs inside jQuery DOM-ready
  handlers (depends on bss-b2b-jquery-341-js inlined earlier in
  theme.liquid), so it runs at DOMContentLoaded regardless of
  defer vs blocking. Defer just unblocks initial paint + lets
  lazysizes hydrate product card images sooner.

  Briefly reverted on 2026-04-26 EOD when an apparent regression
  (TIGI header missing) appeared post-deploy. Root cause was later
  traced to Edge profile-state corruption on the tester's machine,
  unrelated to this defer change — confirmed by reproducing the
  hang in their broken profile both with and without defer, and
  confirming a fresh Edge profile loads cleanly. Re-applying with
  evidence the defer is safe for fresh browsers.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script src="{{ 'bss-b2b-hook.js' | asset_url }}" defer="defer"></script>
<script src="{{ 'bss-b2b-js.js' | asset_url }}" defer="defer"></script>
